parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lag or hesitation in the DCT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate to accelerate, leading to potential accidents, especially when merging into traffic or turning into oncoming traffic.
symptoms: The transmission lags or hesitates to engage when accelerating from a slow speed
resulting in a delay of 1-3 seconds before the vehicle begins to move. This occurs frequently
especially when slowing down and then accelerating again
such as when turning into oncoming traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DCT transmission to downshift can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to potential accidents, especially when merging into traffic or turning into oncoming traffic.
symptoms: The transmission fails to downshift when slowing down
resulting in a loss of power and acceleration. This occurs frequently
especially when slowing down and then accelerating again
such as when turning into oncoming traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall Delays and Unavailability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailability of Takata airbag replacements can lead to a significant risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbags may explode or fail to deploy properly.
symptoms: None
as the issue is related to the recall and replacement process rather than a specific symptom or malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty passenger restraint system can cause the airbag to malfunction or not deploy properly, leading to an increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Error message: "Fault in - Passenger Restraint System affecting airbag
belt tensioner
or belt force limiter."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
all electrical systems are dead despite a good battery
gauges bottom out quickly and then return to normal
warning lights appear on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience uncontrolled acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locking system can cause the doors to stick or not unlock, potentially trapping the driver or passengers inside the vehicle, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door locking bolt sticks up partially when pulling the handle
but does not unlock
requiring the use of the lock button on the dashboard to unlock the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tail light socket can cause the tail lights and blinkers to malfunction, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The tail light socket overheats due to improper grounding
causing the tail lights and blinkers to malfunction.
